cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.COMM, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the optimization of a linear feedback scheme for a concatenated code over an AWGN channel with noisy feedback. This involves analyzing the information capacity of the channel and optimizing the feedback scheme to improve the error rate performance of the code. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of feedback in a communication system, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. The implementation of a feedback transmission scheme as an inner code in a concatenated code is also relevant to this sub-category. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The use of feedback in control systems is a well-known concept in this sub-category. The paper's investigation of a linear feedback scheme for a concatenated code can be seen as a control system that aims to minimize errors in the transmission of information. 
4. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper's focus on improving the error rate performance of a communication system through the use of concatenated coding and feedback is relevant to this sub-category. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - While not as likely as the previous sub-categories, the paper's use of low density parity check (LDPC) and turbo codes in simulations to display practical applications and their error rate benefits can be seen as a data structures and algorithms
